id: AIC-NAV-001
type: module
owner: business
extends: project.intent

module: aic navigate
command: aic navigate --query "your task description"
description: >
  Traverses the project intent structure based on a natural language
  query and assembles a scoped context package containing exactly
  the right intent files for that task.
  No AI involved. No code generated. Pure deterministic traversal.
  Output is ready to paste into any AI tool.

behaviors:
  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B1
    intent: |
      Parse the query to extract:
        - Component name if mentioned
        - Language if mentioned
        - Action type (fix, create, migrate, explain, audit)
      If component name is ambiguous list all matching
      business folders and ask developer to clarify.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B2
    intent: |
      Always read project.intent first.
      It is always in scope for every query without exception.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B3
    intent: |
      Match query to the most relevant subfolder in /business.
      Read that module.intent and any referenced sub-intents.
      If no match found list all available business modules
      and ask developer to clarify.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B4
    intent: |
      If language is specified in query read that language.intent.
      If language not specified and only one language exists use it.
      If multiple languages exist and none specified ask developer.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B5
    intent: |
      Read all component.intent files under the matched
      language and business module combination.
      If multiple components exist under one module
      include all of them — they share the same business context.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B6
    intent: |
      Assemble all read intent files into one clean context block.
      Add a header line describing what the context covers.
      Add a footer line instructing how to use the context.
      Output to terminal by default.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B7
    intent: |
      Support output flags:
        --copy    copies output to clipboard automatically
        --file    writes output to .aic/context/{query-slug}.txt
        --compile pipes directly to aic compile

journeys:
  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "fix account lockout in android"
    outcome: |
      Scoped context assembled containing:
        project.intent
        /business/UserService/module.intent
        /android/android.intent
        /android/UserService/UserService.intent
      Printed to terminal ready to paste into AI.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "fix account lockout" with no language
    outcome: |
      AIC detects multiple languages in project.
      Lists available languages and asks developer to specify.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "something completely unrelated"
    outcome: |
      No matching business module found.
      Lists all available business module folder names.
      Asks developer to clarify or pick from list.

  - actor: Autonomous AI agent
    trigger: Reads NAVIGATION.intent from .aic/intent-lib/ directly
    outcome: |
      Follows step by step navigation instructions.
      Self-navigates to correct context without running aic navigate.
      Used when AIC is not installed in the environment.

output-format: |
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  AIC CONTEXT: fix account lockout in android
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  [project.intent contents]
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  [module.intent contents]
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  [android.intent contents]
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  [UserService.intent contents]
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Paste this context into your AI before describing your task.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────

implementation-note: |
  This command contains zero LLM calls.
  All phases are fully deterministic.
  Phase 1: query parsing
  Phase 2: file traversal
  Phase 3: context assembly
  Phase 4: output formatting
  No AI provider configuration required to run this command.